  "prompt": "What's the worst game you ever played?",
  "response": "Okay, buckle up, because I have a strong contender for the worst game I've ever played:\n\n**\"Superman 64\" for the Nintendo 64.**\n\nLet me explain why this game is notorious and why it earned the top spot on my personal \"worst of\" list:\n\n*   **The Rings:** The gameplay is almost entirely centered around flying through rings. Not epic battles, not saving Metropolis, just endlessly, frustratingly flying through poorly rendered rings in a fog-filled environment. The controls are terrible, making even the simplest maneuvers a chore. These rings made this game a torture and the main reason why people hate this game.\n\n*   **Terrible Controls:** Superman, the Man of Steel, controls like a block of lead covered in molasses. He's sluggish, unresponsive, and difficult to steer. Flying is supposed to be empowering, but in this game, it's an exercise in patience and frustration.\n\n*   **Graphics and Fog:** Even by N64 standards, the graphics are bad. The draw distance is ridiculously short, shrouded in a thick fog that obscures everything. It's hard to see where you're going or what you're supposed to do.\n\n*   **Story:** The story is convoluted and nonsensical. Lex Luthor traps Superman in a virtual reality world, forcing him to complete arbitrary tasks. The plot feels tacked on and serves only to justify the repetitive and uninspired gameplay.\n\n*   **Repetitive and Boring:** The missions are almost all the same: fly through rings, punch some generic enemies, and repeat. There's no variety, no sense of progression, and no feeling of accomplishment.\n\n*   **Broken Physics:** The game is riddled with glitches and bugs. Superman often gets stuck on objects, falls through the floor, or behaves in unpredictable ways.\n\nBasically, \"Superman 64\" is a perfect storm of bad design, technical problems, and uninspired gameplay. It fails to capture the essence of the Superman character and delivers a deeply unsatisfying experience.\n\nWhile there might be other games out there with specific flaws that are equally egregious, \"Superman 64\" is a standout example of a game that just fails on almost every level. It's a legendary bad game for a reason.",
